    • implement

      public void implement​(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token. Generated class classes name should be same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java
      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar​(Class<?> token, Path jarFilePath) throws ImplerException
      Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token. Generated class classes name should be same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added.
      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFilePath - target .jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.
